hopobject.body: Languages callion pharma llc The decision set October 21 as the deadline for the state to begin to issue marriage licenses to couples in New Jersey, but Republican Governor Chris Christie said, through a spokesperson, that he would appeal to the state supreme court. That supreme court ruled in 2006 that same-sex couples should have the same rights as straight couples but allowed the legislature to decide whether those rights could be granted through marriage or some other scheme. The legislature chose civil unions.
